    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"connections\" and \"joy\" are just temporary chemical spikes in a brain that's eventually going to die anyway. it's just a distraction from the reality of the void. if the end result is always just total non-existence and nothingness, then striving to keep going just feels like a waste of energy. why fight for a momentary spark in an infinite dark?",
